From 231f69b894550edbf9332d65a6c0bd035222d691 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bryan Casler <bryan.casler@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 16:03:18 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] avfilter/vf_deflicker: fix comparator used for median mode

The qsort comparator compared the element pointers themselves
(aa - bb) instead of the pointed-to values, so AV_QSORT never
actually sorted the luminance window and median mode returned an
arbitrary element of the unsorted window instead of its median.

Reproduce with a clip whose per-frame average luminance repeats
40, 200, 120, 80: with size=5 every window's median is 80 or 120,
but the filter's lavfi.deflicker.new_luminance metadata reports
80, 40, 200, 120 (an unsorted window slot):

  ffmpeg -f lavfi -i "color=c=black:s=64x64:r=25:d=0.8,format=gray,\
geq=lum='if(eq(mod(N\,4)\,0)\,40\,if(eq(mod(N\,4)\,1)\,200\,\
if(eq(mod(N\,4)\,2)\,120\,80)))'" \
    -vf deflicker=size=5:mode=median,metadata=mode=print -f null -

After this change the reported new_luminance matches the true
window median for every frame; all other modes are unaffected.

Signed-off-by: Bryan Casler <bryan.casler@gmail.com>
---
 libavfilter/vf_deflicker.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/libavfilter/vf_deflicker.c b/libavfilter/vf_deflicker.c
index 38f838f..22b25d0 100644
--- a/libavfilter/vf_deflicker.c
+++ b/libavfilter/vf_deflicker.c
@@ -298,7 +298,7 @@ static void get_pm_factor(AVFilterContext *ctx, float *f)
 static int comparef(const void *a, const void *b)
 {
     const float *aa = a, *bb = b;
-    return round(aa - bb);
+    return FFDIFFSIGN(*aa, *bb);
 }
 
 static void get_median_factor(AVFilterContext *ctx, float *f)
